<h1>Push Notifications</h1>

<h2>Web Push</h2>

Web Push is supported by the WebPushService.  The enable web push you need to configure a VAPID key pair

<code>
$ npx web-push generate-vapid-keys --json
</code>

Then in your app/deployment services.jrl configure the WebPushService

<code>
p({
  "class":"foam.core.boot.CSpec",
  "name":"WebPushService",
  "lazy":true,
  "serve":false,
  "authenticate":false,
  "service":{
    "class":"foam.core.notification.push.WebPushService",
    "supportEmail": "some-support@email",
    "publicKey": "public key generated by web-push",
    "privateKey": "private key generated by web-push"
  }
})
</code>

<h2>APNS (Apple) Push</h2>

<p>
APNS push is supported by he APNSPushService in core.
</p>

<ol>
<li>
To setup APNS push notification support, you need to first register your app with Apple
<a href="https://developer.apple.com/documentation/usernotifications/registering-your-app-with-apns"/>
</li>

<li>
Then you need to obtain an SSL client certificate for authenticated to APNS from core.
<a href="https://developer.apple.com/documentation/usernotifications/establishing-a-certificate-based-connection-to-apns"/>
</li>

<li>
<p>You then need to put your certificate and the associated private key into a .p12 file.   If you followed instructions on the
above link, you can export a .p12 from the Keychain Access app on macOS by finding the certificate, right clicking and selecting "export"
</p>
</li>

<li>
Convert the .p12 file to base64 using the shell
<code>
$ base64 -b 70 < push-credentials.p12 > push-credentials.p12.txt
</code>
</li>

<li>
Save your apns credentials into a credentials.jrl file in your app/deployment
<code>
p({
  "class": "foam.core.notification.push.APNSCredential",
  "id": "apns-sandbox-creds",
  "host": "api.sandbox.push.apple.com",
  "appBundleId": "my.app.bundle.id",
  "p12Password": "password",
  "p12Base64": """
  RUtx+68Ctaqhaa5vFI7iUPG2IXo7hhPgSqFScdY02Rm9k4cQmeIaL3bfi2U3HwXi4msS+v
  uIf4roiUOg3Us8m8RgHOkZr/GAbxDRqBS8DnD5PXbAp1VscBvvxI1cOG3bkd3ept5+TAQ/
  jiVUqIsD0RhKdrpJ3UZ0naD...
"""
})
</code>
</li>

<li>
Finally configure the APNSpushService to use the newly created credentials
<code>
p({
  "class":"foam.core.boot.CSpec",
  "name":"APNSpushService",
  "lazy":true,
  "serve":false,
  "service":{
    "class":"foam.core.notification.push.APNSPushService",
    "apnsCredentialId": "apns-sandbox-creds"
  }
})
</code>
</li>
</ol>
